I used to be a radish hater...not after this recipe. The radishes get a sweet flavor from roasting. Did cut the oil a bit, just enough to coat the vegies. Yummy, healthy, and easy to make.

Rating: 4
As a combination, this worked well--excellent with a squeeze of lemon. I think the key is not overcooking the radishes so they retain a bit of firmness and their taste doesn't mellow too much. I only added enough oil to just coat the vegetables. I could see this being really tasty cold tossed with pasta or tortellini, lemon and a bit of feta or shaved parm.

