The bite from the radishes completely goes away and is replaced by a sweet caramelized flavour. This was absolutely delicious.

Rating: 4
Excellent way to use a huge bunch of big radishes. I roasted at 400 on a foil-lined baking sheet. I halved the recipe and added olive oil and salt until it looked correct. (We roast vegetables all the time.) 20-30 minutes appears to be correct even at 400. Some of my radishes were the size of medium turnips and very pithy when cut. They still tasted great after roasting.